1
[C]Blessing eter[Dm]nal c[G]omes from the [F]Triune [C]God; 
Father, Son,[Em] Spi[Am]rit, [D7]our portion [Gsus4 G]free;
[C]What gift of [F]favor, [C]what guarding [Am Dm]power; 
[G]What wealth[G7] of [C]mer[F]cy, [G7]what perfect [C  F C]peace!

2
Eternal Father, source of each blessing;
Bestowed on Christ from heaven above;
In Your name keep us, with Your hand hold us;
From evil shield us, safe in Your love!

3
Eternal Son arose as the morning sun;
God in the flesh brought glory and grace;
Your presence touched us, Your kindness reached us;
Shine now upon us, light of your face!

4
Eternal Spirit, lift up Your countenance,
Flow within us as rivers of peace;
Your eyes assure us, Your gaze inspires us;
Your smile approves us, what guarantee!

5
Praise to You, Father, for care almighty;
Praise to You, Son, for amazing grace;
Praise to You, Spirit, for peace abiding;
Blessing eternal, ours to embrace!

6
The love of God, the grace of Christ Jesus,
Fellowship of the Spirit divine;
Be with us now, and be with us ever;
Blessing and praise shall soon intertwine!

